transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling, this is John, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, I'm calling about the prescription that you guys filled for me.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: I was supposed to get what I understood, the new Viagra, the new VGA, or AGB,

Speaker 1: and I got a generic form of...

Speaker 2: So, if we screwed up, we'll fix it for you, sir. I need your name and zip code to start, though.

Speaker 1: Okay. Jeff Brown, 98374.

Speaker 2: Thank you, one second, Jeff.

Speaker 1: No problem.

Speaker 2: 120 to have and fuel up?

Speaker 1: That is correct.

Speaker 2: Okay. You have the pills with you right now, by chance?

Speaker 1: I do.

Speaker 2: Can you just read to me the stamp on one of the pills itself, because that will confirm one way or the other for me.

Speaker 1: Oh, the stamp on it?

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: Let's see, just a second here.

Speaker 2: No problem.

Speaker 1: I'm driving, so...

Speaker 2: It says AC-335.

Speaker 1: Okay. That tells me what I need to know. Your pill should have said 50.

Speaker 2: So, you're right. It was the regular generic, not the AGB.

Speaker 1: So, you don't have to return that to us, because it was our mistake, but I am going to get you the right pill, sir.

Speaker 2: So, I'm going to message the pharmacy. They will get you ten of the right ones.

Speaker 1: There's no charge. You've already paid us.

Speaker 2: Oh, okay. Great. Thank you.

Speaker 1: You're welcome. Sorry about the mix-up, but thank you for letting us know.

Speaker 2: Oh, no problem. Thank you very much.

Speaker 1: Of course. Have a good weekend.

Speaker 2: You, too. Bye-bye.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.
